s23-hw4.pdf

  • You can test your stdiox.c using the checker file and input file, as well as an expected output file. Place them in the same directory as your stdiox.c:
    • checker.c 
    • stdin-1
    • stdout_expected-2
    • Note that checker.c has passed compilation with solution, so if you cannot pass compilation, you need to check your code;
  • To use them, compile and invoke your program from terminal: 
    • gcc checker.c stdiox.c
    • ./a.out < stdin-1 > stdout
  • Your output file stdout should match stdout_expected-2, except the output of long text file which is random;
  • Note that matching the expected output doesn't mean you'll receive full credits. This is only for your own testing. See PDF description for other requirements.
